- I'll give you 14.

693
00:47:32,249 --> 00:47:35,343
- He's offering me 14 for this!
- Fifteen!

694
00:47:35,419 --> 00:47:38,752
Seventeen. My last word. I won't take
a penny less, or strike me dead.

695
00:47:38,822 --> 00:47:40,653
- Sixteen.
- Done.

696
00:47:40,724 --> 00:47:42,783
Nice to do business with you.

697
00:47:42,860 --> 00:47:45,852
- I'll throw you in this as well.
- I don't want it, but thanks.

698
00:47:45,929 --> 00:47:48,159
- Burt.
- All right, all right.

699
00:47:48,232 --> 00:47:50,962
- Now, where's the 16 you owe me?
- I just gave you 20.

700
00:47:51,034 --> 00:47:53,798
- Right. That's four I owe you, then.
- That's right. That's fine.

701
00:47:53,871 --> 00:47:56,271
- I've got it here somewhere.
- That's four for the gourd.

702
00:47:56,340 --> 00:47:58,968
Four? For this gourd?

703
00:47:59,042 --> 00:48:01,909
Look at it! It's worth ten
if it's worth a shekel.

704
00:48:01,979 --> 00:48:05,244
- You gave it to me for nothing.
- Yes, but it's worth ten.

705
00:48:05,315 --> 00:48:07,112
All right, all right.

706
00:48:09,686 --> 00:48:12,018
No, no, no, no.
It's not worth ten.

707
00:48:12,089 --> 00:48:15,718
You're supposed to argue.
"Ten for that? You must be mad. "

708
00:48:18,428 --> 00:48:21,864
Oh, well.
One born every minute.

709
00:48:21,932 --> 00:48:23,923
- Daniel.
- Daniel.

