- My legs are old and bent.

772
00:51:50,674 --> 00:51:52,608
My ears are grizzled. Yes?

773
00:51:52,676 --> 00:51:55,873
There's one place
we didn't look. Guards!

774
00:51:55,946 --> 00:52:00,042
- I'm just a poor old man.
- [Clattering]

775
00:52:00,117 --> 00:52:02,051
My nose is knackered.

776
00:52:02,119 --> 00:52:04,553
Have you ever seen
anyone crucified?

777
00:52:04,621 --> 00:52:06,953
Crucifixion's a doddle.

778
00:52:07,023 --> 00:52:08,957
Don't keep saying that.

779
00:52:09,025 --> 00:52:11,459
[Clattering]

780
00:52:13,763 --> 00:52:16,061
Found this spoon, sir.

781
00:52:16,133 --> 00:52:18,363
Well done, sergeant.

782
00:52:18,435 --> 00:52:21,927
We'll be back, oddball.

783
00:52:24,374 --> 00:52:26,501
[Officer Knocks]
Open up!

784
00:52:26,576 --> 00:52:29,101
You haven't given us
time to hide.

785
00:52:29,179 --> 00:52:31,909
[Screaming]

786
00:52:31,982 --> 00:52:34,109
[Grunts, Groans]

787
00:52:41,224 --> 00:52:45,024
- In that time...
- The serpent, he shall strike you...

788
00:52:45,095 --> 00:52:49,555
- Holes from every bitch you got germs from...
- Jumbo jets...

789
00:52:53,803 --> 00:52:56,499
Don't pass judgement
on other people...

790
00:52:56,573 --> 00:52:58,700
or you might
get judged yourself.

791
00:52:58,775 --> 00:53:02,404
- What?
- I said, don't pass judgement on other people...

792
00:53:02,479 --> 00:53:05,209
or else you might
get judged too.

793
00:53:05,282 --> 00:53:07,147
- Who, me?
- Yes.

794
00:53:07,217 --> 00:53:10,380
- Thank you very much.
- Not just you. All of you.

795
00:53:10,453 --> 00:53:12,785
- That's a nice gourd.
- What?

796
00:53:12,856 --> 00:53:15,347
- How much do you want for the gourd?
- You can have it.

797
00:53:15,425 --> 00:53:18,155
- Have it?
- Yes. Consider the lilies.

798
00:53:18,228 --> 00:53:20,458
- Don't you want to haggle?
- No. In the field.

799
00:53:20,530 --> 00:53:22,760
- What's wrong with it?
- Nothing. Take it.

800
00:53:22,832 --> 00:53:25,960
- Consider the lilies?
- Well, the birds, then.

801
00:53:26,036 --> 00:53:27,970
- What birds?
- Any birds.

802
00:53:28,038 --> 00:53:30,598
- Why?
- Well, have they got jobs?

803
00:53:30,674 --> 00:53:32,608
- Who?
- The birds.

804
00:53:32,676 --> 00:53:34,610
Have the birds got jobs?

805
00:53:34,678 --> 00:53:38,239
- What's the matter with him?
- Says the birds are scrounging.

806
00:53:38,315 --> 00:53:41,250
The point is, the birds,
they do all right, don't they?

807
00:53:41,318 --> 00:53:44,116
- Well, good luck to 'em.
- Yeah, they're very pretty.

808
00:53:44,187 --> 00:53:48,146
Okay. And you're much more
important than they are, right?

809
00:53:48,225 --> 00:53:50,989
So what are you worrying about?
There you are. See?

810
00:53:51,061 --> 00:53:53,723
I'm worrying about what
you've got against birds.

811
00:53:53,797 --> 00:53:55,890
I haven't got anything
against the birds.

812
00:53:55,966 --> 00:53:58,901
- Consider the lilies.
- He's having a go at the flowers now!

813
00:53:58,969 --> 00:54:01,904
- Give the flowers a chance.
- I'll give you one for it.

814
00:54:01,972 --> 00:54:04,167
- It's yours.
- Two, then.

815
00:54:04,241 --> 00:54:06,539
Look, there was this man,
and he had two servants.

816
00:54:06,610 --> 00:54:09,340
What were they called?
What were their names?

817
00:54:09,412 --> 00:54:11,937
I don't know.
And he gave them some talents.

818
00:54:12,015 --> 00:54:14,711
- You don't know?
- Well, it doesn't matter.

819
00:54:14,784 --> 00:54:16,843
He doesn't know
what they were called!

820
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:20,185
- They were called Simon and Adrian.
- You said you didn't know!

821
00:54:20,257 --> 00:54:23,317
It really doesn't matter. The point is,
there were these two servants.

822
00:54:23,393 --> 00:54:26,362
- He's making it up as he goes along.
- No, I'm not!

823
00:54:26,429 --> 00:54:28,693
And he gave them...
Wait, were there three?

824
00:54:28,765 --> 00:54:31,131
- Oh, he's terrible.
- [Blows Raspberry]

825
00:54:31,201 --> 00:54:34,637
- There were two or three.
- Oh, get off!

826
00:54:37,674 --> 00:54:40,404
[Stammering]

827
00:54:40,477 --> 00:54:43,275
Now hear this!
Blessed are they...

828
00:54:43,346 --> 00:54:45,610
- Three.
- Who convert their neighbor's asses.

829
00:54:45,682 --> 00:54:49,448
- For they shall inhibit their girth.
- Rubbish!

830
00:54:49,519 --> 00:54:52,784
- And to them only shall be given...
- [Soldiers Leaving]

831
00:54:52,856 --> 00:54:56,087
To them only...

832
00:54:56,159 --> 00:54:59,959
shall be given...

833
00:55:01,831 --> 00:55:03,765
- What?
- Hmm?

834
00:55:03,833 --> 00:55:06,461
- Shall be given what?
- Oh, nothing.

835
00:55:06,536 --> 00:55:08,936
- What were you going to say?
- Nothing.

836
00:55:09,005 --> 00:55:11,337
- Yes, you were going to say something.
- No, I finished.

837
00:55:11,408 --> 00:55:14,502
- Tell us before you go.
- I'm finished.

838
00:55:14,577 --> 00:55:16,875
- No, you don't.
- Why won't he tell?

839
00:55:16,946 --> 00:55:19,608
- Won't say!
- It ain't a secret, is it?

840
00:55:19,683 --> 00:55:22,481
- Must be, otherwise he'd tell us.
- Tell us.

841
00:55:22,552 --> 00:55:24,577
- Leave me alone.
- What is the secret?

842
00:55:24,654 --> 00:55:27,054
- Is it the secret of eternal life?
- He won't say.

843
00:55:27,123 --> 00:55:29,853
If I knew the secret
of eternal life, I wouldn't say.

844
00:55:29,926 --> 00:55:32,451
- Leave me alone!
- Just tell me, please.

845
00:55:32,529 --> 00:55:35,430
- We were here first.
- [Indistinct Shouting]

846
00:55:35,498 --> 00:55:38,092
- Go away!
- Tell us, master.

847
00:55:38,168 --> 00:55:41,137
- Is that his gourd?
- Yeah, but it's under offer.

848
00:55:41,204 --> 00:55:43,331
This is his gourd.

849
00:55:43,406 --> 00:55:46,603
- Ten!
- It is his gourd!

850
00:55:46,676 --> 00:55:49,645
We will carry it
for you, master.

851
00:55:49,713 --> 00:55:53,205
- Master?
- He's gone!

852
00:55:53,283 --> 00:55:55,683
- He's been taken up.
- [Gasps]

853
00:55:55,752 --> 00:55:57,811
[Together]
He's been taken up!

854
00:55:57,887 --> 00:56:00,754
- Nineteen!
- No, there he is. Over there.

855
00:56:02,292 --> 00:56:06,422
[Indistinct Shouting]

856
00:56:13,470 --> 00:56:16,405
¤ [Choir Vocalizing]

857
00:56:27,016 --> 00:56:29,314
Look! Oh! Oh!

858
00:56:29,386 --> 00:56:31,320
He has given us a sign.

859
00:56:31,388 --> 00:56:33,788
He has given us his shoe!

860
00:56:33,857 --> 00:56:36,655
The shoe is the sign.
Let us follow his example.

861
00:56:36,726 --> 00:56:40,924
- What?
- Let us, like him, hold up one shoe!

862
00:56:40,997 --> 00:56:45,195
For this is his sign that all
who follow him shall do likewise!

863
00:56:45,268 --> 00:56:47,793
- Yes!
- No, no. The shoe is a sign...

864
00:56:47,871 --> 00:56:51,034
that we must gather shoes
together in abundance.

865
00:56:51,107 --> 00:56:53,632
Cast off the shoes.
Follow the gourd!

866
00:56:53,710 --> 00:56:56,736
No, let us gather shoes
together! Let me!

867
00:56:56,813 --> 00:57:01,182
No, it is a sign that, like him, we must
think not of the things of the body...

868
00:57:01,251 --> 00:57:03,185
but of the face and head.

869
00:57:03,253 --> 00:57:05,847
- Give me your shoe!
- Get off!

870
00:57:05,922 --> 00:57:09,358
Follow the gourd,
the Holy Gourd of Jerusalem!

871
00:57:09,426 --> 00:57:13,089
- The gourd!
- Hold up the sandal, as he has commanded us.

872
00:57:13,163 --> 00:57:15,791
- It is a shoe!
- It's a sandal!

873
00:57:15,865 --> 00:57:18,333
- No, it isn't!
- Cast it away!

874
00:57:18,401 --> 00:57:20,335
- Put it on!
- Clear off!

875
00:57:20,403 --> 00:57:22,997
Take the shoes
and follow him!

876
00:57:23,072 --> 00:57:25,632
[Indistinct Shouting]

877
00:57:28,912 --> 00:57:31,642
Come back! Stop!

878
00:57:31,714 --> 00:57:35,172
Let us... Let us pray.

879
00:57:36,352 --> 00:57:39,219
Yea, he cometh to us...

880
00:57:39,289 --> 00:57:41,587
like the seeds of the grain.

881
00:58:00,577 --> 00:58:03,876
[Chattering, Shouting]

882
00:58:03,947 --> 00:58:07,678
Master! Master!

883
00:58:29,572 --> 00:58:32,598
Hey! Is there
another way down?

884
00:58:33,810 --> 00:58:36,301
Is there another path
down to the river?

885
00:58:36,379 --> 00:58:39,678
Please, please help me.
I've got to get...

886
00:58:39,749 --> 00:58:42,013
[Shouting Continues]

887
00:58:43,286 --> 00:58:46,380
Oh, my foot! Oh...

888
00:58:46,456 --> 00:58:49,755
- Shhh.
- Oh, damn, damn, damn!

889
00:58:49,826 --> 00:58:53,387
- I'm sorry.
- Oh, damn, damn it! Blast it!

890
00:58:53,463 --> 00:58:55,727
- I'm sorry. Shhh.
- Don't you "shhh" me.

891
00:58:55,798 --> 00:58:58,824
Eighteen years of total silence,
and you "shhh" me!

892
00:58:58,902 --> 00:59:02,065
- What?
- I've kept my vow for 18 years...

893
00:59:02,138 --> 00:59:06,165
Not a single, recognizable,
articulate sound has passed my lips.

894
00:59:06,242 --> 00:59:08,802
Could you be quiet
for another five minutes?

895
00:59:08,878 --> 00:59:11,506
It doesn't matter now.
I might as well enjoy myself.

896
00:59:11,581 --> 00:59:14,345
For the last 18 years,
I've wanted to shout...

897
00:59:14,417 --> 00:59:17,147
and sing and scream
my name out!

898
00:59:17,220 --> 00:59:19,313
- Shhh. Shhh.
- Oh, I'm alive!

899
00:59:19,389 --> 00:59:22,483
¤ Hava nagila, hava nagila ¤

900
00:59:22,559 --> 00:59:25,392
¤ Hava nagila... ¤

901
00:59:25,461 --> 00:59:29,124
Oh, I'm alive! I'm alive!
Hello, birds. Hello, trees.

902
00:59:29,198 --> 00:59:31,962
I'm alive! I'm alive!

903
00:59:32,035 --> 00:59:36,938
¤ Hava nagila
Hava n'ra, n'ra... ¤

904
00:59:37,006 --> 00:59:40,498
Master! Master! Master!

905
00:59:40,577 --> 00:59:44,069
- Master!
- The master! He is here!

906
00:59:44,147 --> 00:59:48,516
- His shoe led us to him!
- [All Shouting]

907
00:59:48,585 --> 00:59:52,282
Speak! Speak to us, master.
Speak to us!

908
00:59:52,355 --> 00:59:54,050
Go away!

909
00:59:54,123 --> 00:59:56,751
[Together]
A blessing! A blessing!

910
00:59:56,826 --> 00:59:59,260
How shall we go away, master?

911
00:59:59,329 --> 01:00:01,763
Oh, just go away
and leave me alone!

912
01:00:01,831 --> 01:00:03,992
Give us a sign!

913
01:00:04,067 --> 01:00:07,366
He has given us a sign!
He has brought us to this place!

914
01:00:07,437 --> 01:00:10,270
I didn't bring you here.
You just followed me.

915
01:00:10,340 --> 01:00:13,400
Oh, it's still a good sign
by any standard.

916
01:00:13,476 --> 01:00:16,411
Master, your people
have walked many miles to be with you!

917
01:00:16,479 --> 01:00:18,470
They are weary
and have not eaten.

918
01:00:18,548 --> 01:00:20,675
It's not my fault
they haven't eaten.

919
01:00:20,750 --> 01:00:23,218
There is no food
in this high mountain!

920
01:00:23,286 --> 01:00:26,517
What about the juniper
bushes over there?

921
01:00:26,590 --> 01:00:30,253
[All Gasp]
A miracle! A miracle!

922
01:00:30,327 --> 01:00:34,661
He has made the bush
fruitful by his words!

923
01:00:34,731 --> 01:00:37,131
They've brought forth
juniper berries.

924
01:00:37,200 --> 01:00:40,897
Of course! They're juniper bushes!
What do you expect!

925
01:00:40,971 --> 01:00:43,064
Show us another miracle.

926
01:00:43,140 --> 01:00:45,233
Do not tempt him, shallow ones!

927
01:00:45,308 --> 01:00:49,005
Is not the miracle of
the juniper bushes enough?

