can you get?

1050
01:08:16,059 --> 01:08:18,323
Now, piss off!

1051
01:08:19,596 --> 01:08:21,791
- She is.
- Yeah, definitely.

1052
01:08:21,864 --> 01:08:24,799
[Chattering Continues]

1053
01:08:26,669 --> 01:08:29,103
- [Door Closes]
- Morning, Savior.

1054
01:08:29,172 --> 01:08:32,630
[Indistinct Shouting]

1055
01:08:38,982 --> 01:08:41,075
Lay your hands
on me, quick!

1056
01:08:41,150 --> 01:08:44,415
Now, don't jostle
the Chosen One, please.

1057
01:08:44,487 --> 01:08:48,514
Don't push that baby
in the Savior's face.

1058
01:08:48,591 --> 01:08:52,220
I say, could you just
see my wife?

1059
01:08:52,295 --> 01:08:54,354
You'll have to wait,
I'm afraid.

1060
01:08:54,430 --> 01:08:56,864
We've got
a luncheon appointment.

1061
01:08:56,933 --> 01:08:58,924
The lepers are queuing.

1062
01:08:59,002 --> 01:09:01,869
My brother-on-law
is the ex-mayor of Gath!

1063
01:09:01,938 --> 01:09:06,102
Brian, can I introduce the gentleman
who's letting us have the Mounts on Sunday?

1064
01:09:06,175 --> 01:09:11,306
- Don't push!
- And keep the noise down!

1065
01:09:11,381 --> 01:09:16,512
Those possessed by devils,
try and keep them under control.

1066
01:09:16,586 --> 01:09:19,419
Incurables, you'll just
have to wait for a few minutes.

1067
01:09:19,489 --> 01:09:24,085
Um, women taken in sin, line up
against that wall, will you?

1068
01:09:24,160 --> 01:09:28,961
Brian? Brian,
you were fantastic.

1069
01:09:29,032 --> 01:09:31,159
You weren't so bad yourself.

1070
01:09:31,234 --> 01:09:34,226
No. What you said just now.
It was quite extraordinary.

1071
01:09:34,303 --> 01:09:36,237
What?
All that, was it?

1072
01:09:36,305 --> 01:09:38,432
